      <hedline>
        <hl1>Jerusalem's Future: A Capital of Peace; Jewish History</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Dave Crystal letter on Karen Armstrong's July 16 article holds Jews have aborigional historic claims to Jerusalem</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Karen Armstrong (Op-Ed, July 16) misrepresents the core issue of Jerusalem by couching it in religious terms. Jerusalem is the undivided capital of Israel today because it was the undivided capital of Israel 3,000 years ago. One does not have to believe in God to recognize this historic fact. Besides the Jews, no other people has aboriginal historic claims to the city of Jerusalem.</p>
        <p>DAVE CRYSTAL  Staten Island, July 17, 2000</p>
      </block>
